@page "/about"
@attribute [Authorize]
@rendermode InteractiveServer

<PageTitle>About – Family Vault</PageTitle>

<h1>About Family Vault</h1>
<p class="vault-page-subtitle">
    Your private, secure hub for managing your family's financial life — across borders, across generations.
</p>

@* ── Hero banner ── *@
<div class="vault-about-hero">
    <div class="vault-about-hero__icon" aria-hidden="true">🔒</div>
    <div class="vault-about-hero__body">
        <h2 class="vault-about-hero__title">One place. Everything your family needs.</h2>
        <p class="vault-about-hero__text">
            Family Vault brings together your assets, documents, insurance policies, nominees, tax records,
            and estate planning into a single, always-available platform — so that the people you love are
            never left in the dark when it matters most.
        </p>
    </div>
</div>

@* ── Why use it ── *@
<h2 class="vault-about-section-heading">Why use Family Vault?</h2>

<div class="vault-about-reasons">

    <div class="vault-about-reason">
        <span class="vault-about-reason__icon" aria-hidden="true">🛡️</span>
        <div>
            <h3 class="vault-about-reason__title">Protect what matters most</h3>
            <p class="vault-about-reason__text">
                Accidents and illness do not announce themselves. Family Vault ensures that your spouse,
                children, or nominated contacts can instantly find account numbers, policy details, and
                emergency contacts — reducing panic and legal delays at the worst possible time.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="vault-about-reason">
        <span class="vault-about-reason__icon" aria-hidden="true">🌏</span>
        <div>
            <h3 class="vault-about-reason__title">Multi-jurisdiction asset tracking</h3>
            <p class="vault-about-reason__text">
                Built for families with ties to both the <strong>UK</strong> and <strong>India</strong>.
                Track UK savings accounts, ISAs, and pensions alongside Indian NRE/NRO accounts,
                mutual funds, and property — all in one dashboard, with the right currency and
                tax context for each country.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="vault-about-reason">
        <span class="vault-about-reason__icon" aria-hidden="true">📊</span>
        <div>
            <h3 class="vault-about-reason__title">Know your readiness score</h3>
            <p class="vault-about-reason__text">
                The <strong>Family Readiness Score</strong> gives you a 0–100 rating based on whether you have
                nominees registered, wills in place, an emergency fund, and key documents uploaded.
                It tells you exactly where your gaps are and what to fix first.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="vault-about-reason">
        <span class="vault-about-reason__icon" aria-hidden="true">🚨</span>
        <div>
            <h3 class="vault-about-reason__title">Emergency Mode for trusted people</h3>
            <p class="vault-about-reason__text">
                Emergency Mode presents a concise, read-only summary of critical information — account
                locations, insurance contacts, will executors, and nominee details — designed for a
                trusted family member or solicitor who needs fast access during a crisis.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="vault-about-reason">
        <span class="vault-about-reason__icon" aria-hidden="true">💡</span>
        <div>
            <h3 class="vault-about-reason__title">Smart, actionable insights</h3>
            <p class="vault-about-reason__text">
                The dashboard analyses your data and highlights real risks: insurance policies without a
                named beneficiary, assets held in repatriation-restricted accounts, income sources that
                may not be declared in the right jurisdiction, and more.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="vault-about-reason">
        <span class="vault-about-reason__icon" aria-hidden="true">🔐</span>
        <div>
            <h3 class="vault-about-reason__title">Secure by design</h3>
            <p class="vault-about-reason__text">
                Access is controlled by your organisation's <strong>Microsoft Entra ID (Azure AD)</strong>
                identity — the same login you already trust. Role-based policies ensure that family
                members only see what they are authorised to see, and all data is stored in Azure
                with encryption at rest and in transit.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>

</div>

@* ── How to use it ── *@
<h2 class="vault-about-section-heading">How to use Family Vault</h2>
<p class="vault-page-subtitle">Work through the sections below in roughly this order when you first get started.</p>

<div class="vault-about-steps">

    <div class="vault-about-step">
        <div class="vault-about-step__number" aria-hidden="true">1</div>
        <div class="vault-about-step__body">
            <h3 class="vault-about-step__title">
                <span aria-hidden="true">👤</span> Set up My Profile
            </h3>
            <p class="vault-about-step__text">
                Navigate to <strong>My Profile</strong> and fill in your personal details, date of birth,
                address, and spouse or partner information. Add your children and emergency contacts here too.
                This information is used to populate nominee records and Emergency Mode.
            </p>
            <NavLink href="/profile" class="vault-btn vault-btn--secondary vault-btn--sm">
                Go to My Profile →
            </NavLink>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="vault-about-step">
        <div class="vault-about-step__number" aria-hidden="true">2</div>
        <div class="vault-about-step__body">
            <h3 class="vault-about-step__title">
                <span aria-hidden="true">🏦</span> Add your UK &amp; India assets
            </h3>
            <p class="vault-about-step__text">
                Use <strong>UK Assets</strong> to record savings accounts, ISAs, cash, and pensions held in
                the United Kingdom. Use <strong>India Assets</strong> to record NRE/NRO accounts, fixed
                deposits, mutual funds, PPF, and other Indian holdings — including repatriation status and
                tax residency implications.
            </p>
            <div class="vault-about-step__links">
                <NavLink href="/uk-assets" class="vault-btn vault-btn--secondary vault-btn--sm">UK Assets →</NavLink>
                <NavLink href="/india-assets" class="vault-btn vault-btn--secondary vault-btn--sm">India Assets →</NavLink>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="vault-about-step">
        <div class="vault-about-step__number" aria-hidden="true">3</div>
        <div class="vault-about-step__body">
            <h3 class="vault-about-step__title">
                <span aria-hidden="true">🏛</span> Record Bank Accounts &amp; Investments
            </h3>
            <p class="vault-about-step__text">
                <strong>Bank Accounts</strong> lets you register every current, savings, salary, or fixed-deposit
                account with its institution, masked account number, and country. <strong>Investments</strong>
                covers stocks, mutual funds, pensions, and crypto — giving you a portfolio summary by type.
            </p>
            <div class="vault-about-step__links">
                <NavLink href="/bank-accounts" class="vault-btn vault-btn--secondary vault-btn--sm">Bank Accounts →</NavLink>
                <NavLink href="/investments" class="vault-btn vault-btn--secondary vault-btn--sm">Investments →</NavLink>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="vault-about-step">
        <div class="vault-about-step__number" aria-hidden="true">4</div>
        <div class="vault-about-step__body">
            <h3 class="vault-about-step__title">
                <span aria-hidden="true">🛡️</span> Add Insurance Policies
            </h3>
            <p class="vault-about-step__text">
                Record every life, health, critical illness, and income-protection policy under
                <strong>Insurance</strong>. The app will warn you whenever a policy has no named nominee — a
                common oversight that can delay pay-outs significantly. Keep renewal dates here so nothing
                lapses unnoticed.
            </p>
            <NavLink href="/insurance" class="vault-btn vault-btn--secondary vault-btn--sm">
                Go to Insurance →
            </NavLink>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="vault-about-step">
        <div class="vault-about-step__number" aria-hidden="true">5</div>
        <div class="vault-about-step__body">
            <h3 class="vault-about-step__title">
                <span aria-hidden="true">🏠</span> Track Property &amp; Loans
            </h3>
            <p class="vault-about-step__text">
                Use <strong>Property &amp; Loans</strong> to register residential or commercial properties in the
                UK or India, along with any outstanding mortgages or loans linked to each one. Rows with
                an active loan are highlighted so you and your family can see liabilities at a glance.
            </p>
            <NavLink href="/properties" class="vault-btn vault-btn--secondary vault-btn--sm">
                Go to Property &amp; Loans →
            </NavLink>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="vault-about-step">
        <div class="vault-about-step__number" aria-hidden="true">6</div>
        <div class="vault-about-step__body">
            <h3 class="vault-about-step__title">
                <span aria-hidden="true">🚨</span> Build your Emergency Fund
            </h3>
            <p class="vault-about-step__text">
                <strong>Emergency Fund</strong> lets you log where your liquid reserves are held and in what
                currency. Enter your estimated monthly household expenses and the app tells you how many
                months of cover you have — with clear good / warning / low indicators. The recommended
                minimum is 3–6 months of expenses.
            </p>
            <NavLink href="/emergency-fund" class="vault-btn vault-btn--secondary vault-btn--sm">
                Go to Emergency Fund →
            </NavLink>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="vault-about-step">
        <div class="vault-about-step__number" aria-hidden="true">7</div>
        <div class="vault-about-step__body">
            <h3 class="vault-about-step__title">
                <span aria-hidden="true">🧾</span> Register Nominees
            </h3>
            <p class="vault-about-step__text">
                <strong>Nominees</strong> is the most critical section for family protection. For every major
                asset — bank account, insurance policy, pension, investment — record who the legal nominee
                is. The Dashboard will flag any asset type that is missing a nominee so you can close
                the gap quickly.
            </p>
            <NavLink href="/nominees" class="vault-btn vault-btn--secondary vault-btn--sm">
                Go to Nominees →
            </NavLink>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="vault-about-step">
        <div class="vault-about-step__number" aria-hidden="true">8</div>
        <div class="vault-about-step__body">
            <h3 class="vault-about-step__title">
                <span aria-hidden="true">🧮</span> Summarise your Tax Position
            </h3>
            <p class="vault-about-step__text">
                <strong>Tax Summary</strong> lets you record income sources, the amounts involved, and
                whether each has been declared to the relevant tax authority (HMRC or IT Department of India).
                Undeclared entries are highlighted in amber so you always know your compliance status.
            </p>
            <NavLink href="/tax-summary" class="vault-btn vault-btn--secondary vault-btn--sm">
                Go to Tax Summary →
            </NavLink>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="vault-about-step">
        <div class="vault-about-step__number" aria-hidden="true">9</div>
        <div class="vault-about-step__body">
            <h3 class="vault-about-step__title">
                <span aria-hidden="true">⚖️</span> Record Wills &amp; Legal Documents
            </h3>
            <p class="vault-about-step__text">
                Under <strong>Wills &amp; Legal</strong>, record whether a valid will exists for each
                jurisdiction you hold assets in (UK and/or India), where the original is stored, who
                the executor is, and the name of your solicitor. The app displays a prominent critical
                banner for any jurisdiction where no will is recorded — because dying intestate can
                cost your family years and thousands in legal fees.
            </p>
            <NavLink href="/wills-legal" class="vault-btn vault-btn--secondary vault-btn--sm">
                Go to Wills &amp; Legal →
            </NavLink>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="vault-about-step">
        <div class="vault-about-step__number" aria-hidden="true">10</div>
        <div class="vault-about-step__body">
            <h3 class="vault-about-step__title">
                <span aria-hidden="true">📁</span> Upload Documents
            </h3>
            <p class="vault-about-step__text">
                Use <strong>Upload</strong> to attach scanned copies of passports, wills, property deeds,
                insurance certificates, and any other important papers. Documents are stored securely in
                Azure Blob Storage and can be browsed and downloaded from <strong>My Documents</strong>.
                Supported formats: PDF, PNG, JPG, JPEG, DOCX, TXT (up to 20 MB each).
            </p>
            <div class="vault-about-step__links">
                <NavLink href="/upload" class="vault-btn vault-btn--secondary vault-btn--sm">Upload a document →</NavLink>
                <NavLink href="/documents" class="vault-btn vault-btn--secondary vault-btn--sm">My Documents →</NavLink>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="vault-about-step">
        <div class="vault-about-step__number" aria-hidden="true">11</div>
        <div class="vault-about-step__body">
            <h3 class="vault-about-step__title">
                <span aria-hidden="true">🆘</span> Review Emergency Mode
            </h3>
            <p class="vault-about-step__text">
                Once your data is populated, open <strong>Emergency Mode</strong> and review what a trusted
                family member would see in a crisis. This read-only view surfaces the most important
                information — bank locations, insurance contacts, will executors, and emergency
                fund sources — without exposing sensitive figures unnecessarily.
                Share the URL with a spouse or trusted contact so they know it exists.
            </p>
            <NavLink href="/emergency" class="vault-btn vault-btn--secondary vault-btn--sm">
                Preview Emergency Mode →
            </NavLink>
        </div>
    </div>

</div>

@* ── Readiness score breakdown ── *@
<h2 class="vault-about-section-heading">Understanding your Readiness Score</h2>

<div class="vault-about-score-breakdown">
    <p class="vault-page-subtitle">
        The score is calculated from four equally-weighted pillars (25 points each).
        A score of 80 or above is considered <strong>good</strong>. 50–79 is a <strong>warning</strong>.
        Below 50 needs <strong>urgent attention</strong>.
    </p>
    <div class="vault-about-pillars">
        <div class="vault-about-pillar vault-about-pillar--nominees">
            <span class="vault-about-pillar__icon" aria-hidden="true">🧾</span>
            <span class="vault-about-pillar__label">Nominees</span>
            <span class="vault-about-pillar__points">25 pts</span>
            <p class="vault-about-pillar__hint">At least one nominee registered across your assets.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="vault-about-pillar vault-about-pillar--emergency">
            <span class="vault-about-pillar__icon" aria-hidden="true">🚨</span>
            <span class="vault-about-pillar__label">Emergency Fund</span>
            <span class="vault-about-pillar__points">25 pts</span>
            <p class="vault-about-pillar__hint">At least £1,000 (or equivalent) in accessible liquid savings.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="vault-about-pillar vault-about-pillar--wills">
            <span class="vault-about-pillar__icon" aria-hidden="true">⚖️</span>
            <span class="vault-about-pillar__label">Wills</span>
            <span class="vault-about-pillar__points">25 pts</span>
            <p class="vault-about-pillar__hint">A valid will recorded for every jurisdiction you hold assets in.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="vault-about-pillar vault-about-pillar--documents">
            <span class="vault-about-pillar__icon" aria-hidden="true">📁</span>
            <span class="vault-about-pillar__label">Documents</span>
            <span class="vault-about-pillar__points">25 pts</span>
            <p class="vault-about-pillar__hint">At least one document uploaded to the vault.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

@* ── Quick tips ── *@
<h2 class="vault-about-section-heading">Tips for getting the most out of Family Vault</h2>

<ul class="vault-about-tips">
    <li>
        <span aria-hidden="true">✅</span>
        <strong>Start with the Dashboard.</strong> The Readiness Score and Smart Insights tell you exactly
        what to tackle first — use them as your to-do list.
    </li>
    <li>
        <span aria-hidden="true">🔄</span>
        <strong>Review annually.</strong> Set a reminder every year to update insurance renewal dates,
        nominee details, and your emergency fund balance. Life changes — your vault should too.
    </li>
    <li>
        <span aria-hidden="true">📄</span>
        <strong>Upload originals or certified copies.</strong> A scanned will or insurance certificate
        stored here is accessible from anywhere, even if the physical copy is lost in a fire or flood.
    </li>
    <li>
        <span aria-hidden="true">👨‍👩‍👧</span>
        <strong>Tell your family it exists.</strong> Emergency Mode is only useful if a trusted person
        knows to look here. Make sure your spouse or a close family member has access and knows the URL.
    </li>
    <li>
        <span aria-hidden="true">🏴󠁧󠁢󠁳󠁣󠁴󠁿</span>
        <strong>Don't forget India assets.</strong> Many NRI families discover after a bereavement that
        funds are locked in NRO accounts due to missing nominations or expired tax clearances.
        Record these assets and their nominees now.
    </li>
    <li>
        <span aria-hidden="true">⚠️</span>
        <strong>Act on critical banners immediately.</strong> A missing-will or missing-nominee banner
        is not a cosmetic warning — it signals a real legal risk. Treat these as urgent actions.
    </li>
</ul>
